This is the documentation for PyCDFT.
The documentation consists of the following:
1. pycdft-manual.pdf: detailed description of classes and attributes
2. classes.pdf: UML summarizing pycdft-manual.pdf
3. packages.pdf: UML summarizing flow of parts within pycdft module

pycdft-manual.pdf is generated using Doxygen + doxypypy
(http://www.stack.nl/~dimitri/doxygen/index.html; https://github.com/Feneric/doxypypy)
classes.pdf and package.pdf is generated using pyreverse
(https://www.logilab.org/blogentry/6883)

----------------------------------------------------
For midway, you can load the following useful modules:
>> module load doxygen texlive qt graphviz

doxypypy can be downloaded using:
>> git clone https://github.com/Feneric/doxypypy.git

Make sure the /path/to/doxypypy/lib/ folder with site-packages is in $PYTHONPATH

The file py_filter must with in $PATH

-----------------------------------------------------
The configuration for how Doxygen documents the source files 
can be edited in <doxygen.config>

To generate a new set of documentation, simply run:
>> doxygen doxygen.config

